The paper discusses the use of deep learning methods in healthcare, specifically for medical image classification tasks. This suggests that the paper could fall under several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

Firstly, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a likely category as the paper discusses the use of distributed machine learning methods to mitigate the problem of limited labeled data in healthcare. 

Secondly, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also a likely category as the paper focuses on medical image classification tasks using deep learning methods. 

Thirdly, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper discusses the use of deep neural networks for medical image classification tasks. 

Fourthly, cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is a possible category as the paper discusses the challenges of conducting multi-center collaborative studies in healthcare and proposes a solution using distributed machine learning methods. 

Finally, cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possible category as the paper focuses on medical image classification tasks using deep learning methods.
